FT  08 JAN 94 / Finance and the Family: Pep charges cut or waived - At a
glance
Fund managers are aiming to attract new investors looking for tax shelters
before the end of the tax year by cutting or waiving charges on Peps.
Clerical Medical is cutting the initial charge on its unit trust Peps from
5.25 per cent to 2.5 per cent for lump sum investments of more than Pounds
1,000 made between January 10 and April 5. There are five unit trusts to
choose from. Annual charges are 1.25 per cent on two of them, and 1.5 per
cent on the others.
Finsbury Asset Management is waiving all charges on its Peps until further
notice, and new Peps will be charge-free for their lifetime. Investors can
choose from four Finsbury investment trusts.
